<subSubSection id="C36A65251463221B23E3FC120EC86C67" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCF36AE1463221B23E3FC120EC86C67" blockId="6.[151,1436,930,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B904EABC1463221B23E3FC120F666B8F" bold="true" box="[198,326,970,996]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsal fin origin distinctly behind anal fin origin; pectoral fin-rays 19–21; precaudal vertebrae 25–29.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36A65251463221B23E3FBC20FA96CEF" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCF36AE1463221B23E3FBC20FA96CEF" blockId="6.[151,1436,930,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B904EABC1463221B23E3FBC20F476C5F" bold="true" box="[198,359,1050,1076]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Distribution.</emphasis>
Western South Atlantic and South Pacific. In the western Atlantic, it is known from 
<collectingRegion id="49B4F84C1463221B261AFBC20EFD6C37" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F367763E1463221B23CCFB9A0F106C37" box="[233,304,1090,1116]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(present study) to Tierra del Fuego and 
<collectingCountry id="F367763E1463221B202FFB9A0A236C37" box="[778,1027,1090,1116]" name="South Georgia Island" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">South Georgia Island</collectingCountry>
(Markle &amp; Olney 1990), at depths from 
<quantity id="4C889B4B1463221B23F2FBB20FA46CEF" box="[215,388,1130,1156]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.205" metricValueMax="14.41" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="920.5" valueMax="1441.0" valueMin="400.0">400 to 1441 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36A65251463221B23E3FB4A0B596CBF" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCF36AE1463221B23E3FB4A0B596CBF" blockId="6.[151,1436,930,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B904EABC1463221B23E3FB4A0F1F6CC7" bold="true" box="[198,319,1170,1196]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 370-mm specimen represents the northernmost (
<geoCoordinate id="EE4450691463221B209CFB4A0A366CC7" box="[953,1046,1170,1196]" degrees="19" direction="south" minutes="49" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" precision="925" value="-19.816668">19°49'S</geoCoordinate>
) and deepest (
<quantity id="4C889B4B1463221B27E6FB4A0B3F6CC7" box="[1219,1311,1170,1196]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.441" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="1441.0">1441 m</quantity>
) record of the species. Previously reported off southern 
<collectingCountry id="F367763E1463221B218DFB620CD06CBF" box="[680,752,1210,1236]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B5F1463221B203EFB620A0A6CBF" author="Marke, D. F. &amp; Olney, J. E." box="[795,1066,1210,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" pagination="269 - 410" refId="ref16960" refString="Marke, D. F. &amp; Olney, J. E. (1990) Systematics of the pearlfishes (Pisces: Carapidae). Bulletin of Marine Science, 47 (2), 269 - 410." type="journal article" year="1990">Marke &amp; Olney (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B5F1463221B2746FB620B566CBF" author="Bernardes, R. A. &amp; Figueiredo, J. L. &amp; Rodrigues, A. R. &amp; Fischer, L. G. &amp; Vooren, C. M. &amp; Haimovici, M. &amp; Wongtschowski, C. L. D. B." box="[1123,1398,1210,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refId="ref15057" refString="Bernardes, R. A., Figueiredo, J. L., Rodrigues, A. R., Fischer, L. G., Vooren, C. M., Haimovici, M. &amp; Rossi- Wongtschowski, C. L. D. B. (2005) Peixes da Zona Economica Exclusiva da regiao sudeste-sul do Brazil. Levantamento com armadilhas, pargueiras e rede de arrasto de fundo. Edusp, Sao Paulo, 295 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Bernardes 
<emphasis id="B904EABC1463221B27C7FB630B356CBF" box="[1250,1301,1211,1236]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">et al</emphasis>
. (2005)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
